The paper addresses the problem of unsupervised disentanglement of factors of data, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of variational autoencoders and the proposed alternating minimization approach suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
